{
	"id": "a1-unit-07",
	"cefrLevel": "A1",
	"order": 7,
	"title": "Questions et négation — Asking & saying no",
	"objective": "Ask simple questions and make negative statements (A1: can ask and answer simple questions on familiar topics).",
	"bridge": {
		"title": "Bridge from Hindi / English: negation wraps the verb (ne … pas)",
		"body": "French negation has TWO parts around the verb: **ne** + verb + **pas**. *Je ne parle pas anglais* = “I don’t speak English.” In speech, the **ne** is often dropped (*je parle pas*), but write both. To ask a yes/no question, just add **est-ce que** at the front: *Est-ce que tu parles français ?* Hindi puts नहीं after the verb and questions often use क्या at the front — similar instincts, different words."
	},
	"cards": [
